Hide editor tab strip right-side action icons (PRO-5559)

Force the editor tab strip to never populate the right-side actions
toolbar — "Open in split editor", "More actions" and the `…` overflow
menu — regardless of any user override of
`workbench.editor.editorActionsLocation`.

`updateEditorActionsToolbar` short-circuits before it asks the group
view for actions, so no menu commands are wired up. The toolbar
container itself is left in place (the layout reserves the slot via
`createEditorActionsToolBar`) and close-on-active and other tab
behaviour is untouched.

Index: code-server/lib/vscode/src/vs/workbench/browser/parts/editor/editorTabsControl.ts
===================================================================
